[1]
Date: Thu 25 Feb 2021
Source: CGTN / Xinhua News Agency [edited]
https://newsaf.cgtn.com/news/2021-02-26/Burkina-Faso-plans-free-immunization-to-curb-anthrax-spread-Yb6EQzCrU4/index.html


Burkina Faso's government has announced to mobilize 4000 doses of anthrax vaccines for free immunization to curb the spread of the disease in the country.

On 22 Jan 2021, Burkina Faso confirmed the outbreak of anthrax disease in Gueguere commune, Ioba province, in southwest of the country.

The statement reported that the disease has devastated livestock and caused the death of 2 people after the consumption of infected animals.

