[Anthrax is sporadic but widespread in Burkina Faso and was not unknown in Ioba province in the past It is unfortunate that as this disease becomes less frequent, the villagers forget the risks involved in butchering and eating the meat from dead cattle. Thus, these human fatal cases, and the importance of maintaining public awareness of the risk.

When new outbreaks occur, one must revert to the policy of regularly vaccinating the cattle in and around affected villages and rural communities. The outbreaks concurring from owner stupidity is a good gauge of continuing risk.

Gueguere is a department, or commune, of Ioba province, Sud-Ouest region, in southwest Burkina Faso (see Wikipedia:
(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gu%C3%A9gu%C3%A9r%C3%A9_%28department%29).
- Mod.MHJ

